Six years ago this June.

541
01:13:42,600 --> 01:13:48,914
How was that possible?
- Oh, I ask the Lord that every day.

542
01:13:50,000 --> 01:13:55,393
Doctors blamed genetics but I don't
know. She was small...

543
01:13:55,560 --> 01:13:58,711
and weaker than
the other children.

544
01:13:58,880 --> 01:14:03,431
But I had faith that
God would protect her.

545
01:14:07,000 --> 01:14:12,552
Angela believed in her own
kind of protection.

546
01:14:14,120 --> 01:14:18,910
An angel?
- Faith is all-powerful.

547
01:14:19,080 --> 01:14:24,916
If one truly believes in something,
one will make it come true.

548
01:14:26,720 --> 01:14:32,477
Of course, we have to be careful
what we choose to believe in.

549
01:14:33,160 --> 01:14:37,870
Duty calls. Forgive me.
I'll be right back.

550
01:14:47,600 --> 01:14:51,957
Hey, you play any football?
- Do I play football?

551
01:14:52,120 --> 01:14:53,872
Toss here, kid.

552
01:14:55,360 --> 01:15:00,036
You see this arm? In Jefferson County,
it's worth more than your life.

553
01:15:02,800 --> 01:15:05,598
Nice arm. For a girl.

554
01:15:06,640 --> 01:15:08,471
Kid, hey kid.

555
01:15:33,480 --> 01:15:35,357
You gotta be kidding me?

556
01:15:42,240 --> 01:15:45,471
Hey kid, I've got your ball.

557
01:15:52,200 --> 01:15:54,350
Speak, you little bastard.

558
01:16:22,280 --> 01:16:23,952
What are you doing?

559
01:16:26,840 --> 01:16:30,389
Did you know about these?
- What are they?

560
01:16:30,560 --> 01:16:33,120
Why would she draw these?

561
01:16:34,560 --> 01:16:37,279
Those can't be Angela's.

562
01:16:49,080 --> 01:16:50,957
Just in case.

563
01:16:57,080 --> 01:16:58,718
Hey kid, is that you?

564
01:17:01,720 --> 01:17:05,599
What is this thing?
- I don't know.

565
01:17:07,120 --> 01:17:08,712
Whatever it is...

566
01:17:10,400 --> 01:17:12,038
it's real.

567
01:19:05,040 --> 01:19:07,429
What in God's name?

568
01:19:11,680 --> 01:19:13,477
Who are you?

569
01:19:20,320 --> 01:19:23,915
He's gone.

570
01:19:25,880 --> 01:19:31,318
What happened? Are you okay?
- It's too late. It's too late.

571
01:19:32,400 --> 01:19:35,358
Look at this.
- I don't understand. What's going on?

572
01:19:35,520 --> 01:19:39,195
It is the ghost.
- Ghost? What ghost?

573
01:19:39,360 --> 01:19:42,511
From the game.
- Who are you?

574
01:19:42,680 --> 01:19:46,309
You're not Angela's friend.
What do you want from her?

575
01:19:46,480 --> 01:19:49,517
She's suffered enough.
- You get out of here.

576
01:19:49,680 --> 01:19:53,150
Leave the poor girl in peace.
- God sees you, Ms. Channing.

577
01:19:53,320 --> 01:19:55,754
God sees everything.

578
01:20:03,680 --> 01:20:09,073
Who was that lady? And what the hell were you doing
out here in the middle of the freaking night?

579
01:20:10,120 --> 01:20:14,193
It doesn't matter anymore.
They're all gone, it's over.

580
01:20:14,360 --> 01:20:18,353
Sandy, nobody knows where you've been.

581
01:20:20,200 --> 01:20:24,034
If you're in some kind of trouble,
you can talk to me.

582
01:20:24,200 --> 01:20:28,876
It doesn't matter anymore, Eli. It doesn't matter.
- Stop saying that.

583
01:20:33,480 --> 01:20:36,153
It matters to me.

584
01:20:37,200 --> 01:20:41,318
You're my sister, okay.
If something is going on, please tell me.

585
01:20:41,480 --> 01:20:43,436
So I can help you.

586
01:20:44,880 --> 01:20:46,677
You can trust me.

587
01:20:48,000 --> 01:20:52,232
You know that, right?
- I want you to listen to me, okay.

588
01:20:52,400 --> 01:20:56,791
You do know that I love you and
I would never lie to you ever.

589
01:20:56,960 --> 01:21:01,397
But what I'm about tell you is gonna sound
like the craziest thing in the world, because it is.

590
01:21:01,560 --> 01:21:05,553
And I know you're not gonna believe me, because
nobody believes me. But I need you to believe, Eli.

591
01:21:05,720 --> 01:21:07,199
I'm listening.

592
01:21:09,240 --> 01:21:12,835
When we're little, we used to
play games, you remember?

593
01:21:13,000 --> 01:21:17,596
In the graveyard?
- There was a girl, an orphan. Her name was Angela.

594
01:21:19,160 --> 01:21:25,998
Last night we played the game again, but we
weren't alone. Six people are with us, Eli.

595
01:21:26,160 --> 01:21:32,235
Six of our friends, and I know you don't remember them,
but they were there and now they're gone.

596
01:21:33,360 --> 01:21:37,353
Gone? What do you mean gone?
- Something...

597
01:21:37,520 --> 01:21:40,273
This thing took them.

598
01:21:42,080 --> 01:21:47,313
This thing is connected to
Angela and the game?

599
01:21:47,480 --> 01:21:49,357
It has to be.

600
01:22:04,760 --> 01:22:09,311
I knew you wouldn't believe me.
- I believe you.

601
01:22:13,200 --> 01:22:16,875
I believe you.
Why would you make it up?

602
01:22:17,040 --> 01:22:19,190
I wouldn't.

603
